{"repo": "sabnzbd/sabnzbd", "pull_number": 3350, "instance_id": "sabnzbd__sabnzbd-3350", "issue_numbers": [3055], "base_commit": "40e97400a6e04306180327b3ab3eceafc71268dc", "patch": "diff --git a/sabnzbd/api.py b/sabnzbd/api.py\nindex f875f5017c4..05739e33062 100644\n--- a/sabnzbd/api.py\n+++ b/sabnzbd/api.py\n@@ -564,8 +564,14 @@ def _api_history_default(value: str, kwargs: dict[str, Union[str, list[str]]]) -\n     failed_only = bool_conv(kwargs.get(\"failed_only\"))\n     nzo_ids = clean_comma_separated_list(kwargs.get(\"nzo_ids\"))\n \n+    # Snapshot the counter once to avoid racing with history_updated() calls\n+    # between the staleness check and the response \u2014 if the counter changes\n+    # mid-request the client would record the newer value but receive stale\n+    # data, causing it to skip the real update on the next poll.\n+    current_history_update = sabnzbd.LAST_HISTORY_UPDATE\n+\n     # Do we need to send anything?\n-    if last_history_update == sabnzbd.LAST_HISTORY_UPDATE:\n+    if last_history_update == current_history_update:\n         return report(keyword=\"history\", data=False)\n \n     if failed_only:\n@@ -593,7 +599,7 @@ def _api_history_default(value: str, kwargs: dict[str, Union[str, list[str]]]) -\n         statuses=statuses,\n         nzo_ids=nzo_ids,\n     )\n-    history[\"last_history_update\"] = sabnzbd.LAST_HISTORY_UPDATE\n+    history[\"last_history_update\"] = current_history_update\n     history[\"version\"] = sabnzbd.__version__\n     return report(keyword=\"history\", data=history)\n \ndiff --git a/sabnzbd/misc.py b/sabnzbd/misc.py\nindex 0f26e7bc189..3ea26c2ab54 100644\n--- a/sabnzbd/misc.py\n+++ b/sabnzbd/misc.py\n@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@\n import socks\n import math\n import rarfile\n-from threading import Thread\n+from threading import Thread, RLock\n from collections.abc import Iterable\n from typing import Union, Any, AnyStr, Optional, Collection\n \n@@ -54,7 +54,7 @@\n )\n import sabnzbd.config as config\n import sabnzbd.cfg as cfg\n-from sabnzbd.decorators import conditional_cache\n+from sabnzbd.decorators import conditional_cache, synchronized\n from sabnzbd.encoding import ubtou, platform_btou\n from sabnzbd.filesystem import userxbit, make_script_path, remove_file, strip_extensions\n \n@@ -92,6 +92,9 @@\n # Check if strings are defined for AM and PM\n HAVE_AMPM = bool(time.strftime(\"%p\"))\n \n+# The history counter need to be made atomic to ensure consistency.\n+HISTORY_COUNTER_LOCK = RLock()\n+\n \n def helpful_warning(msg, *args, **kwargs):\n     \"\"\"Wrapper to ignore helpful warnings if desired\"\"\"\n@@ -1470,6 +1473,7 @@ def keep_awake():\n                     sleepless.allow_sleep()\n \n \n+@synchronized(HISTORY_COUNTER_LOCK)\n def history_updated():\n     \"\"\"To make sure we always have a fresh history\"\"\"\n     sabnzbd.LAST_HISTORY_UPDATE += 1\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Inactive 'History' tab text always updates after PP, but not always with correct text, when UI refresh is 1 second\n### SABnzbd version\n\n4.4.0\n\n### Operating system\n\nDebian 12.10\n\n### Using Docker image\n\nNone\n\n### Description\n\nHi guys, I've been seeing this for a while and thought I should do some investigation today so I can report it.  \ud83e\udd13\n\n- Accessing the UI via Firefox 136.0.3 (although, this bug has been around for multiple Debian, Firefox and SABnzbd versions). Also checked this in Chromium 134.0.6998.35 \n- UI access is via HTTP-only on a separate LAN PC.\n- UI theme is glitter-night.\n- UI is using tabbed layout.\n- Python 3.11.2\n- 1GbE LAN. \n- SABnzbd web interface refresh is set to 1 second (**note:** bug does not occur when this is set to 2 seconds). \n\nI have a UI session open in Firefox, and have the 'Queue' (or 'Warnings') tab active. A job completes downloading and passes into the 'History' tab. The history tab text updates and shows \"1 1\" (as-expected) while post-processing occurs. \n\nPost-processing completes, but the 'History' tab text doesn't always update correctly. Sometimes it will show \"1\" (which I think is correct), sometimes it shows \"1 2\" (incorrect). This happens regardless of the exit status of post-processing. The 'History' tab text will stay like this until I refresh/reload the web page (but I assume if another job is processed, it will update itself).  After refresh, the \u2018History\u2019 tab text is \u201c1\u201d.\n\nThis occurs at-random (but only when the tab text should be updated).\n\nWith 2 different browsers open (Firefox and Chromium), it can occur in one browser window and not the other, and appears to be random as-to which browser it is displayed incorrectly.  Sometimes it works fine in both, sometimes it fails in both. \n\n- If I switch the SABnzbd web interface refresh to 2 seconds, it appears to be 100% reliable. 'History' tab text updates correctly to \"1\" on next item processing if the history has been cleared.\n\n- If I have the 'History' tab active when post-processing is complete, it also appears to be 100% reliable. \n\nIn short: the inactive 'History' tab text always updates after post-processing, but not always with the correct text, when the UI refresh is 1 second.\n\nThoughts?\n", "hints_text": "> With 2 different browsers open (Firefox and Chromium), it can occur in one browser window and not the other, and appears to be random as-to which browser it is displayed incorrectly. Sometimes it works fine in both, sometimes it fails in both.\n\nwould seem to suggest a possible browser or cache issue. do you only see it it in firefox? try updating firefox to latest and see it resolve? use a reverse proxy? (if so bypass it to eliminate that variable).  i use 1 sec refresh and firefox myself and cant recall ever seeing this issue myself but ill try and be on the lookout for it.\nCould be a knockout library issue.. Couldn't see obvious bug in our code so far.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "> With 2 different browsers open (Firefox and Chromium), it can occur in one browser window and not the other, and appears to be random as-to which browser it is displayed incorrectly. Sometimes it works fine in both, sometimes it fails in both.\n\nwould seem to suggest a possible browser or cache issue. do you only see it it in firefox? try updating firefox to latest and see it resolve? use a reverse proxy? (if so bypass it to eliminate that variable).  i use 1 sec refresh and firefox myself and cant recall ever seeing this issue myself but ill try and be on the lookout for it.\nCould be a knockout library issue.. Couldn't see obvious bug in our code so far.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/5f2b924ba76dfd7fb08ff83785dc490adbb6bde7"], "created_at": "2026-03-12T23:52:27Z"}
{"repo": "sabnzbd/sabnzbd", "pull_number": 3082, "instance_id": "sabnzbd__sabnzbd-3082", "issue_numbers": [3078], "base_commit": "ccb036ba37bb2bb36ae90345474a45e71a69b356", "patch": "diff --git a/SABnzbd.py b/SABnzbd.py\nindex d568487da35..827ae0f2e91 100755\n--- a/SABnzbd.py\n+++ b/SABnzbd.py\n@@ -39,6 +39,7 @@\n import re\n import gc\n import threading\n+import http.cookies\n from typing import List, Dict, Any\n \n try:\n@@ -1289,6 +1290,9 @@ def main():\n         }\n     )\n \n+    # Monkey-patch key validation to prevent cherrypy from stumbling over invalid cookies\n+    http.cookies._is_legal_key = lambda _: True\n+\n     # Catch shutdown errors that can break cherrypy/cheroot\n     # See https://github.com/cherrypy/cheroot/issues/710\n     try:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "SABnzbd complaining about Tvheadend cookies\n### SABnzbd version\n\n4.5.1\n\n### Operating system\n\nUbuntu 22.04.5 LTS\n\n### Using Docker image\n\nlinuxserver\n\n### Description\n\nSince I added tvheadend to my docker-compose (already containing SAB) I regularly get cookie errors in SAB like these:\n```\n400 Bad Request\n\nIllegal key 'ys-api/channel'\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 761, in process_headers\n    self.cookie.load(value)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 516, in load\n    self.__parse_string(rawdata)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 580, in __parse_string\n    self.__set(key, rval, cval)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 472, in __set\n    M.set(key, real_value, coded_value)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 335, in set\n    raise CookieError('Illegal key %r' % (key,))\nhttp.cookies.CookieError: Illegal key 'ys-api/channel'\n\nDuring handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 659, in respond\n    self._do_respond(path_info)\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 687, in _do_respond\n    self.process_headers()\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 763, in process_headers\n    raise cherrypy.HTTPError(400, str(exc))\ncherrypy._cperror.HTTPError: (400, \"Illegal key 'ys-api/channel'\")\n\nPowered by CherryPy 18.10.0\n```\n\nor\n\n```\n400 Bad Request\n\nIllegal key 'ys-api/mpegts/service'\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 761, in process_headers\n    self.cookie.load(value)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 516, in load\n    self.__parse_string(rawdata)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 580, in __parse_string\n    self.__set(key, rval, cval)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 472, in __set\n    M.set(key, real_value, coded_value)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.12/http/cookies.py\", line 335, in set\n    raise CookieError('Illegal key %r' % (key,))\nhttp.cookies.CookieError: Illegal key 'ys-api/mpegts/service'\n\nDuring handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 659, in respond\n    self._do_respond(path_info)\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 687, in _do_respond\n    self.process_headers()\n  File \"/lsiopy/lib/python3.12/site-packages/cherrypy/_cprequest.py\", line 763, in process_headers\n    raise cherrypy.HTTPError(400, str(exc))\ncherrypy._cperror.HTTPError: (400, \"Illegal key 'ys-api/mpegts/service'\")\n\nPowered by CherryPy 18.10.0 \n```\n\nThese errors can be resolved by deleting the relevant cookies: **ys-api/channel** and/or **ys-api/mpegts/service**\n\nBut it seems those cookies are re-generated by TVHeadend every time when changing column configurations in TVHeadend's \"_Configuration - Channel/EPG - Channels_\" and \"_Configuration - DVB Inputs - Services_\" windows. \n\n```\n192.168.1.xx\tFALSE\t/\tFALSE\t1746296973\tys-api/channel\to%3Acolumns%3Da%253Ao%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A0%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A26%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A1%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A32%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A2%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A32%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A3%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A4%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A43%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A5%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A6%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%25255Ehidden%25253Db%2525253A1%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A7%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A32%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A8%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A43%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A9%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A10%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A43%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A11%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A43%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A12%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A13%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A32%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A14%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A254%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A15%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A16%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A17%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A165%5Esort%3Do%253Afield%253Ds%25253Anumber%255Edirection%253Ds%25253AASC%5Efilters%3Do%253A\n192.168.1.xx\tFALSE\t/\tFALSE\t1746298710\tys-api/mpegts/service\to%3Acolumns%3Da%253Ao%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A0%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A25%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A1%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A25%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A2%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A27%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A3%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A4%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A5%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A6%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A7%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A27%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A8%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%25255Ehidden%25253Db%2525253A1%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A9%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A10%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A11%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A12%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%25255Ehidden%25253Db%2525253A1%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A13%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A14%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A15%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A16%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A17%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A18%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%25255Ehidden%25253Db%2525253A1%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A19%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%25255Ehidden%25253Db%2525253A1%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A20%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A21%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A27%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A22%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A23%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A24%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A139%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A25%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A26%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A36%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A27%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A64%255Eo%25253Aid%25253Dn%2525253A28%25255Ewidth%25253Dn%2525253A64%5Esort%3Do%253Afield%253Ds%25253Asvcname%255Edirection%253Ds%25253AASC%5Efilters%3Do%253Advb_servicetype%253Do%25253Aeq%25253Dn%2525253A1\n```\n\n\nSo the issue is re-occuring as long as both SAB and TVheadend run on the same IP with different ports? But why does SAB complain about them? Does it use the same keys, perhaps?\n\n\n", "hints_text": "because you are putting cookies in the same origin domain `192.168.1.xx` and path `/`, so when sab goes to load cookie for domain its puking on seeing these...   normally not an issue if your segmenting apps to different domains \n*I* am putting cookies? I'd say that's tvheadend setting those. \nYou mean to say you can't run SAB and Tvheadend (or possibly any other software setting cookies) on the same IP? Because SAB is puking seeing cookies it doesn't own? \n\nA very old post on the matter. \nhttps://forums.sabnzbd.org/viewtopic.php?t=12070\nWonder why the suggested edit switching out the CookieError for a pass didn't make it into the code.\nThe tldr is roundabout: You will want to put every app you host under its own subdomain:\nsab.foo.bar for sabnzbd,\nanother.foo.bar for something else.\n\nIf you put both of them on the same Domain and Path, they will make use of the  same Cookie, thats kinda how HTTP works.\nAnyways, imho not a Sabnzbd issue :) \nOver the years, there have been quite a number of reports from users of various other apps conflicting with sab in this way. The reply has mostly been let others solve it, it's too rare, there are ways to navigate this - with additional effort. \n\nBut let me quote what an sabnzbd.org forum admin admitted once upon a time:\n\n> There is a naivet\u00e9 in SABnzbd that makes it assume it's the only cookie owner of the base URL.\n> That's not true when you combine services behind an Apache server.\n> So far we haven't really looked for a solution because it's a rather rare problem and it very probably means that we have to rename all cookies, which is something that won't be appreciated by the 99% of users that are not affected, won't like.\n\nand\n\n> It's a shortcoming of Python's cookie library and of the way CherryPy doesn't handle error situations.\n> SABnzbd reads all cookies related to it's base URL, which isn't completely correct either.\n\nYour suggestion to give every app its own subdomain is really just a workaround for the fact that SABnzbd acts like it owns the root of the domain\u2014like the Highlander, refusing to coexist with anything else, even on a different port. That\u2019s not compatibility; it\u2019s entitlement.\n\nFunny thing is that removing the code in _cprequest.py which actively throws the error seems to solve the issue.\n\n\nSAB stopped vendoring CherryPy in 2017 https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/960494cfa6ff2d67573a08596bc6e517d43c8856 which included the previous fix.\n\nThe best place to get this fixed is in CherryPy itself which after being quiet for years has had a few commits recently. There is a similar issue report about it from 3 years ago https://github.com/cherrypy/cherrypy/issues/1979\n\nWithin SAB there is some desire to [replace CherryPy](https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/issues/2180) but it's a lot of work to probably not change much unless there was a want to change the api/validation or utilise newer techniques such as server-side events or websockets instead of polling.\nThank you for the pointers. Here's hoping that either cherrypy gets reanimated or that sab can find something better.\n\n\nShort of getting tvheadend to fix their junk cookies or cherrypy adding an option to ignore bad cookies, there may be another way. Cherrypy offloads cookie validation to stdlib's http.cookies, which uses [this](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/1d9406e426d95eb088e4a474fccf294cc106b2b6/Lib/http/cookies.py#L172) one liner to determine key validity.\n\nThe internet suggests monkey patching that (see e.g. https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/issues/2683#issuecomment-924559912) so `http.cookies._is_legal_key(\"wot/eva\")` always returns True. Just tested with a patched SABnzbd.py and it does seem to work as advertised, ignoring a fake injected cookie with an invalid key that would otherwise result in a traceback.\n@jcfp wanna make a PR? \ud83d\ude04\n\n", "all_hints_text": "because you are putting cookies in the same origin domain `192.168.1.xx` and path `/`, so when sab goes to load cookie for domain its puking on seeing these...   normally not an issue if your segmenting apps to different domains \n*I* am putting cookies? I'd say that's tvheadend setting those. \nYou mean to say you can't run SAB and Tvheadend (or possibly any other software setting cookies) on the same IP? Because SAB is puking seeing cookies it doesn't own? \n\nA very old post on the matter. \nhttps://forums.sabnzbd.org/viewtopic.php?t=12070\nWonder why the suggested edit switching out the CookieError for a pass didn't make it into the code.\nThe tldr is roundabout: You will want to put every app you host under its own subdomain:\nsab.foo.bar for sabnzbd,\nanother.foo.bar for something else.\n\nIf you put both of them on the same Domain and Path, they will make use of the  same Cookie, thats kinda how HTTP works.\nAnyways, imho not a Sabnzbd issue :) \nOver the years, there have been quite a number of reports from users of various other apps conflicting with sab in this way. The reply has mostly been let others solve it, it's too rare, there are ways to navigate this - with additional effort. \n\nBut let me quote what an sabnzbd.org forum admin admitted once upon a time:\n\n> There is a naivet\u00e9 in SABnzbd that makes it assume it's the only cookie owner of the base URL.\n> That's not true when you combine services behind an Apache server.\n> So far we haven't really looked for a solution because it's a rather rare problem and it very probably means that we have to rename all cookies, which is something that won't be appreciated by the 99% of users that are not affected, won't like.\n\nand\n\n> It's a shortcoming of Python's cookie library and of the way CherryPy doesn't handle error situations.\n> SABnzbd reads all cookies related to it's base URL, which isn't completely correct either.\n\nYour suggestion to give every app its own subdomain is really just a workaround for the fact that SABnzbd acts like it owns the root of the domain\u2014like the Highlander, refusing to coexist with anything else, even on a different port. That\u2019s not compatibility; it\u2019s entitlement.\n\nFunny thing is that removing the code in _cprequest.py which actively throws the error seems to solve the issue.\n\n\nSAB stopped vendoring CherryPy in 2017 https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/960494cfa6ff2d67573a08596bc6e517d43c8856 which included the previous fix.\n\nThe best place to get this fixed is in CherryPy itself which after being quiet for years has had a few commits recently. There is a similar issue report about it from 3 years ago https://github.com/cherrypy/cherrypy/issues/1979\n\nWithin SAB there is some desire to [replace CherryPy](https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/issues/2180) but it's a lot of work to probably not change much unless there was a want to change the api/validation or utilise newer techniques such as server-side events or websockets instead of polling.\nThank you for the pointers. Here's hoping that either cherrypy gets reanimated or that sab can find something better.\n\n\nShort of getting tvheadend to fix their junk cookies or cherrypy adding an option to ignore bad cookies, there may be another way. Cherrypy offloads cookie validation to stdlib's http.cookies, which uses [this](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/1d9406e426d95eb088e4a474fccf294cc106b2b6/Lib/http/cookies.py#L172) one liner to determine key validity.\n\nThe internet suggests monkey patching that (see e.g. https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/issues/2683#issuecomment-924559912) so `http.cookies._is_legal_key(\"wot/eva\")` always returns True. Just tested with a patched SABnzbd.py and it does seem to work as advertised, ignoring a fake injected cookie with an invalid key that would otherwise result in a traceback.\n@jcfp wanna make a PR? \ud83d\ude04\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/dd5b42a3dc2ba5f4e9883cb6cf5af3c87c7a6219", "https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/4cd22ffe7b63b9203576ae7b959acebbd62dc22f"], "created_at": "2025-05-05T09:29:24Z"}
{"repo": "sabnzbd/sabnzbd", "pull_number": 3120, "instance_id": "sabnzbd__sabnzbd-3120", "issue_numbers": [3113], "base_commit": "c562c9a4686b4d5e95e700053d29696256484be9", "patch": "diff --git a/sabnzbd/api.py b/sabnzbd/api.py\nindex 30982b0b3eb..1a5c90f41bf 100644\n--- a/sabnzbd/api.py\n+++ b/sabnzbd/api.py\n@@ -1895,7 +1895,13 @@ def build_history(\n \n def add_active_history(postproc_queue: List[NzbObject], items: List[Dict[str, Any]]):\n     \"\"\"Get the active history queue and add it to the existing items list\"\"\"\n+    nzo_ids = set([nzo[\"nzo_id\"] for nzo in items])\n+\n     for nzo in postproc_queue:\n+        # Skip already in history\n+        if nzo.nzo_id in nzo_ids:\n+            continue\n+\n         # This output has to be the same as fetch_history!\n         item = {\n             \"completed\": int(time.time()),\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/test_api_and_interface.py b/tests/test_api_and_interface.py\nindex 3e42563708c..586f8afae27 100644\n--- a/tests/test_api_and_interface.py\n+++ b/tests/test_api_and_interface.py\n@@ -259,3 +259,25 @@ def test_add_active_history_consistency(self):\n             history_keys = list(history_job.keys())\n             history_keys.sort()\n             assert pp_keys == history_keys\n+\n+    @pytest.mark.usefixtures(\"run_sabnzbd\")\n+    def test_add_active_history_duplicate(self):\n+        \"\"\"Verify that add_active_history does not add duplicate entries\"\"\"\n+        history_db = os.path.join(SAB_CACHE_DIR, DEF_ADMIN_DIR, DB_HISTORY_NAME)\n+        with FakeHistoryDB(history_db) as fake_history:\n+            fake_history.add_fake_history_jobs(1)\n+            jobs, total_items = fake_history.fetch_history()\n+            history_job = jobs[-1]\n+\n+            # Add minimal attributes to create pp-job\n+            nzo = mock.Mock()\n+            nzo.nzo_id = history_job[\"nzo_id\"]\n+            nzo.final_name = \"test_add_active_history\"\n+            nzo.repair, nzo.unpack, nzo.delete = pp_to_opts(choice(list(PP_LOOKUP.keys())))\n+            nzo.download_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(db.HistoryDB.db_path), \"placeholder_downpath\")\n+            nzo.bytes_downloaded = randint(1024, 1024**4)\n+            nzo.unpack_info = {\"unpack_info\": \"placeholder unpack_info line\\r\\n\" * 3}\n+            api.add_active_history([nzo], jobs)\n+\n+            # Make sure the job was not added to the list, a completed entry already exists\n+            assert total_items == len(jobs)\n", "problem_statement": "Occasional calls to history API returning excess entries\n### SABnzbd version\n\n4.5.2\n\n### Operating system\n\nUnraid/Docker\n\n### Using Docker image\n\nlinuxserver\n\n### Description\n\nEvery so often, a call to the SAB history API has been returning two entries for the same NZO_ID, with both of them marked as a status of \"Completed\" but one of them missing the storage path.  Calling the API again shortly after returns only the one entry (the second slot).  Apologies if I'm misunderstanding and this is an intentional response, but I assumed that for a Completed download it should have one history entry and know the final destination.\n\nI can't consistently reproduce the timing that results in this happening, but am getting it in around 1/100 loops of post processing from mylar when it checks the history queue.\n\n```json\n{\n   \"history\":{\n      \"total_size\":\"14.8 T\",\n      \"month_size\":\"412.8 G\",\n      \"week_size\":\"40.9 G\",\n      \"day_size\":\"14.9 G\",\n      \"slots\":[\n         {\n            \"completed\":1752669335,\n            \"name\":\"Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire\",\n            \"nzb_name\":\"Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire.nzb\",\n            \"category\":\"comics\",\n            \"pp\":\"D\",\n            \"script\":\"Default\",\n            \"report\":\"\",\n            \"url\":\"http://servermonkey3.home.arpa:8090/api?apikey=--REDACTED--&cmd=downloadNZB&nzbname=Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire.nzb\",\n            \"status\":\"Completed\",\n            \"nzo_id\":\"SABnzbd_nzo_h4h4kvnz\",\n            \"storage\":\"\",\n            \"path\":\"/media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire\",\n            \"script_line\":\"\",\n            \"download_time\":3,\n            \"postproc_time\":0,\n            \"stage_log\":[\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Source\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"http://servermonkey3.home.arpa:8090/api?apikey=--REDACTED--&cmd=downloadNZB&nzbname=Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire.nzb\"\n                  ]\n               },\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Download\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"Downloaded in 3 seconds at an average of 14.2 MB/s<br/>Age: 3680d\"\n                  ]\n               },\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Servers\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"news.usenetserver.com=46.9 MB\"\n                  ]\n               },\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Repair\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"[Angela-Asgards.Assassin.004.(2015).(Digital).(Zone-Empire)] Quick Check OK\",\n                     \"Trying RAR renamer\"\n                  ]\n               }\n            ],\n            \"downloaded\":49282231,\n            \"completeness\":\"None\",\n            \"fail_message\":\"\",\n            \"url_info\":\"\",\n            \"bytes\":49282231,\n            \"size\":\"47.0 MB\",\n            \"meta\":\"None\",\n            \"series\":\"\",\n            \"duplicate_key\":\"angela\",\n            \"md5sum\":\"\",\n            \"password\":\"None\",\n            \"action_line\":\"Moving: Angela - Asgard's Assassin 004 (2015) (Digital) (Zone-Empire).cbr\",\n            \"loaded\":false,\n            \"retry\":false,\n            \"archive\":false\n         },\n         {\n            \"completed\":1752669335,\n            \"name\":\"Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire\",\n            \"nzb_name\":\"Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire.nzb\",\n            \"category\":\"comics\",\n            \"pp\":\"D\",\n            \"script\":\"Default\",\n            \"report\":\"\",\n            \"url\":\"http://servermonkey3.home.arpa:8090/api?apikey=--REDACTED--&cmd=downloadNZB&nzbname=Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire.nzb\",\n            \"status\":\"Completed\",\n            \"nzo_id\":\"SABnzbd_nzo_h4h4kvnz\",\n            \"storage\":\"/media/downloads/usenet/comics/Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire/Angela - Asgard's Assassin 004 (2015) (Digital) (Zone-Empire).cbr\",\n            \"path\":\"/media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire\",\n            \"script_line\":\"\",\n            \"download_time\":3,\n            \"postproc_time\":0,\n            \"stage_log\":[\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Source\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"http://servermonkey3.home.arpa:8090/api?apikey=--REDACTED--&cmd=downloadNZB&nzbname=Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire.nzb\"\n                  ]\n               },\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Download\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"Downloaded in 3 seconds at an average of 14.2 MB/s<br/>Age: 3680d\"\n                  ]\n               },\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Servers\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"news.usenetserver.com=46.9 MB\"\n                  ]\n               },\n               {\n                  \"name\":\"Repair\",\n                  \"actions\":[\n                     \"[Angela-Asgards.Assassin.004.(2015).(Digital).(Zone-Empire)] Quick Check OK\",\n                     \"Trying RAR renamer\"\n                  ]\n               }\n            ],\n            \"downloaded\":49282231,\n            \"completeness\":\"None\",\n            \"fail_message\":\"\",\n            \"url_info\":\"\",\n            \"bytes\":49282231,\n            \"meta\":\"None\",\n            \"series\":\"None\",\n            \"md5sum\":\"798feef96d14b4d612286f08abc969f8\",\n            \"password\":\"None\",\n            \"duplicate_key\":\"angela\",\n            \"archive\":false,\n            \"size\":\"47.0 MB\",\n            \"action_line\":\"\",\n            \"loaded\":false,\n            \"retry\":false\n         }\n      ],\n      \"ppslots\":1,\n      \"noofslots\":1,\n      \"last_history_update\":15933,\n      \"version\":\"4.5.2\"\n   }\n}\n```\n", "hints_text": "Can you inspect history1.db if the entry is there once or twice? If twice there (which I expect), IMHO it's not the API, but the logging into history1.db. \n\n`~/.sabnzbd/admin$ sqlite3 history1.db .dump | grep -i angela`\n\nor use `sqlitebrowser` for GUI / interactive.\n\nEDIT:\n\n> Calling the API again shortly after returns only the one entry (the second slot).\n\nOh, I missed that. If so, then probably an API problem indeed.\n\n\nNo worries, always worth checking belt and braces.  Only one entry in the DB.\n\nOne other thing I noted was the \"action_line\" entry on the bogus slot, which made me wonder if it was a transactional thing when the status is being updated to completed after the file move, and it's just bad timing to have hit that microsecond as it's upating the status / creating a new history entry for the final completed data.  It would tally with the infrequent nature of the problem.\n> One other thing I noted was the \"action_line\" entry on the bogus slot, which made me wonder if it was a transactional thing when the status is being updated to completed after the file move, and it's just bad timing to have hit that microsecond as it's upating the status / creating a new history entry for the final completed data. It would tally with the infrequent nature of the problem.\n\nIndeed.\n\nAnd the first entry indeed shows  `\"action_line\":\"Moving: ... `, so work in progress?\n\n```\n$ diff 1.json 2.json\n12c12\n<             \"storage\":\"\",\n---\n>             \"storage\":\"/media/downloads/usenet/comics/Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire/Angela - Asgard's Assassin 004 (2015) (Digital) (Zone-Empire).cbr\",\n49d48\n<             \"size\":\"47.0 MB\",\n51,53c50,51\n<             \"series\":\"\",\n<             \"duplicate_key\":\"angela\",\n<             \"md5sum\":\"\",\n---\n>             \"series\":\"None\",\n>             \"md5sum\":\"798feef96d14b4d612286f08abc969f8\",\n55c53,56\n<             \"action_line\":\"Moving: Angela - Asgard's Assassin 004 (2015) (Digital) (Zone-Empire).cbr\",\n---\n>             \"duplicate_key\":\"angela\",\n>             \"archive\":false,\n>             \"size\":\"47.0 MB\",\n>             \"action_line\":\"\",\n57,58c58\n<             \"retry\":false,\n<             \"archive\":false\n---\n>             \"retry\":false\n```\n\n\nthis user came on discord, turns out they have another issue with .cbr wrongly getting viewed as obfuscated rar (CBR/CBZ are, iirc, literally just rars and zips, they just have different extensions to indicate their contents). \n\n```\n2025-07-16 17:05:50,911::DEBUG::[postproc:965] Detected volume-number 340 from RAR-header: /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr \n2025-07-16 17:05:50,915::DEBUG::[postproc:980] Deobfuscate: rarvolnr is: {340: {'/media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr': ['Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-000.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-...\nEmpire)/z.jpg']}}\n...\n2025-07-16 17:05:50,916::DEBUG::[postproc:995] Deobfuscate: Just one obfuscated rarset\n2025-07-16 17:05:50,916::DEBUG::[postproc:1000] Deobfuscate: Renaming /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr to /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug.r338\n```\n\nwhich is fallout of the .cbr being checked and viewed as a rar so when it does the rar header detection in rarvolinfo, it returning that its volume number is 340 (which then logic then goes oh it should be -2 so .r338) then that gets used to rename later on. \nhttps://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/blob/develop/sabnzbd/utils/rarvolinfo.py\n\ntried having them set cbr as ignore extension (config>special>ext_rename_ignore) but did not change the outcome as its not our actual deobfustication stuff but during the rar renamer \nhttps://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/blob/develop/sabnzbd/postproc.py#L963\n\nas .cbr are a little special we might want to guard against these from being checked in the rar_renamer to prevent this. which might end up resolving this other issue as well.. will piece this out to its own issue\nI think it's a timing issue indeed. Right between Post processing finishing and the history item being added. \nWe don't have locking there due to performance. But this is the fallout.\nAlternatively to it being double, it would dissappear while being moved. Also bad..\n> No worries, always worth checking belt and braces. Only one entry in the DB.\n> \n> One other thing I noted was the \"action_line\" entry on the bogus slot, which made me wonder if it was a transactional thing when the status is being updated to completed after the file move, and it's just bad timing to have hit that microsecond as it's upating the status / creating a new history entry for the final completed data. It would tally with the infrequent nature of the problem.\n\nother apps have a few checks to make sure its safe to proceed with sab history items. \n\nonly process if see if status is Failed or Completed\nFor Failed, they check the FailMessage to see why.. then figure out if you want to warn user/remove and retry or whatever. \nFor Completed, they make sure Storage path is not empty (since you cant really process a folder that it is not set). \n\nI'd imagine that this alone would prevent your issue\nFunnily enough I added that latter check as a PR this morning - checks for empty storage on Completed jobs, gives it a little wait before rechecking.  It's been running without hitting this problem again all day in my test environment.  Happy to leave it at that if the alternative is making detrimental changes on the SAB side.\nFrom what I can tell, build_history adds the active entries after getting the finished entries so you could skip the already existing nzo_ids in add_active_history().\n> From what I can tell, build_history adds the active entries after getting the finished entries so you could skip the already existing nzo_ids in add_active_history().\n\nGood idea. Want to implement it?\n\nSorry, this seems like something you'll want new tests for and I hate writing tests.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Can you inspect history1.db if the entry is there once or twice? If twice there (which I expect), IMHO it's not the API, but the logging into history1.db. \n\n`~/.sabnzbd/admin$ sqlite3 history1.db .dump | grep -i angela`\n\nor use `sqlitebrowser` for GUI / interactive.\n\nEDIT:\n\n> Calling the API again shortly after returns only the one entry (the second slot).\n\nOh, I missed that. If so, then probably an API problem indeed.\n\n\nNo worries, always worth checking belt and braces.  Only one entry in the DB.\n\nOne other thing I noted was the \"action_line\" entry on the bogus slot, which made me wonder if it was a transactional thing when the status is being updated to completed after the file move, and it's just bad timing to have hit that microsecond as it's upating the status / creating a new history entry for the final completed data.  It would tally with the infrequent nature of the problem.\n> One other thing I noted was the \"action_line\" entry on the bogus slot, which made me wonder if it was a transactional thing when the status is being updated to completed after the file move, and it's just bad timing to have hit that microsecond as it's upating the status / creating a new history entry for the final completed data. It would tally with the infrequent nature of the problem.\n\nIndeed.\n\nAnd the first entry indeed shows  `\"action_line\":\"Moving: ... `, so work in progress?\n\n```\n$ diff 1.json 2.json\n12c12\n<             \"storage\":\"\",\n---\n>             \"storage\":\"/media/downloads/usenet/comics/Angela.-.Asgards.Assassin.004.2015.Digital.Zone-Empire/Angela - Asgard's Assassin 004 (2015) (Digital) (Zone-Empire).cbr\",\n49d48\n<             \"size\":\"47.0 MB\",\n51,53c50,51\n<             \"series\":\"\",\n<             \"duplicate_key\":\"angela\",\n<             \"md5sum\":\"\",\n---\n>             \"series\":\"None\",\n>             \"md5sum\":\"798feef96d14b4d612286f08abc969f8\",\n55c53,56\n<             \"action_line\":\"Moving: Angela - Asgard's Assassin 004 (2015) (Digital) (Zone-Empire).cbr\",\n---\n>             \"duplicate_key\":\"angela\",\n>             \"archive\":false,\n>             \"size\":\"47.0 MB\",\n>             \"action_line\":\"\",\n57,58c58\n<             \"retry\":false,\n<             \"archive\":false\n---\n>             \"retry\":false\n```\n\n\nthis user came on discord, turns out they have another issue with .cbr wrongly getting viewed as obfuscated rar (CBR/CBZ are, iirc, literally just rars and zips, they just have different extensions to indicate their contents). \n\n```\n2025-07-16 17:05:50,911::DEBUG::[postproc:965] Detected volume-number 340 from RAR-header: /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr \n2025-07-16 17:05:50,915::DEBUG::[postproc:980] Deobfuscate: rarvolnr is: {340: {'/media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr': ['Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-000.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-...\nEmpire)/z.jpg']}}\n...\n2025-07-16 17:05:50,916::DEBUG::[postproc:995] Deobfuscate: Just one obfuscated rarset\n2025-07-16 17:05:50,916::DEBUG::[postproc:1000] Deobfuscate: Renaming /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr to /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug.r338\n```\n\nwhich is fallout of the .cbr being checked and viewed as a rar so when it does the rar header detection in rarvolinfo, it returning that its volume number is 340 (which then logic then goes oh it should be -2 so .r338) then that gets used to rename later on. \nhttps://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/blob/develop/sabnzbd/utils/rarvolinfo.py\n\ntried having them set cbr as ignore extension (config>special>ext_rename_ignore) but did not change the outcome as its not our actual deobfustication stuff but during the rar renamer \nhttps://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/blob/develop/sabnzbd/postproc.py#L963\n\nas .cbr are a little special we might want to guard against these from being checked in the rar_renamer to prevent this. which might end up resolving this other issue as well.. will piece this out to its own issue\nI think it's a timing issue indeed. Right between Post processing finishing and the history item being added. \nWe don't have locking there due to performance. But this is the fallout.\nAlternatively to it being double, it would dissappear while being moved. Also bad..\n> No worries, always worth checking belt and braces. Only one entry in the DB.\n> \n> One other thing I noted was the \"action_line\" entry on the bogus slot, which made me wonder if it was a transactional thing when the status is being updated to completed after the file move, and it's just bad timing to have hit that microsecond as it's upating the status / creating a new history entry for the final completed data. It would tally with the infrequent nature of the problem.\n\nother apps have a few checks to make sure its safe to proceed with sab history items. \n\nonly process if see if status is Failed or Completed\nFor Failed, they check the FailMessage to see why.. then figure out if you want to warn user/remove and retry or whatever. \nFor Completed, they make sure Storage path is not empty (since you cant really process a folder that it is not set). \n\nI'd imagine that this alone would prevent your issue\nFunnily enough I added that latter check as a PR this morning - checks for empty storage on Completed jobs, gives it a little wait before rechecking.  It's been running without hitting this problem again all day in my test environment.  Happy to leave it at that if the alternative is making detrimental changes on the SAB side.\nFrom what I can tell, build_history adds the active entries after getting the finished entries so you could skip the already existing nzo_ids in add_active_history().\n> From what I can tell, build_history adds the active entries after getting the finished entries so you could skip the already existing nzo_ids in add_active_history().\n\nGood idea. Want to implement it?\n\nSorry, this seems like something you'll want new tests for and I hate writing tests.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/558f03b70def82e812b4d7524e8b9ab5facd12a0", "https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/a94799672710cfbcf3ca92b3e93b46e3008349d1"], "created_at": "2025-07-31T15:43:04Z"}
{"repo": "sabnzbd/sabnzbd", "pull_number": 3115, "instance_id": "sabnzbd__sabnzbd-3115", "issue_numbers": [3114], "base_commit": "d1948071fc92d916b00ed73adad9e1ada0e9da40", "patch": "diff --git a/sabnzbd/postproc.py b/sabnzbd/postproc.py\nindex f6910d5feb6..c92bb08d0b6 100644\n--- a/sabnzbd/postproc.py\n+++ b/sabnzbd/postproc.py\n@@ -947,6 +947,10 @@ def rar_renamer(nzo: NzbObject) -> int:\n         if not os.path.isfile(file_to_check):\n             continue\n \n+        # guard against cbr files due to pr#3114\n+        if get_ext(file_to_check) == \".cbr\":\n+            continue\n+\n         if rarfile.is_rarfile(file_to_check):\n             # if a rar file is fully encrypted, rarfile.RarFile() will return an empty list:\n             if not rarfile.RarFile(file_to_check, single_file_check=True).filelist():\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "guard against cbr in rar renamer\n> this user came on discord, turns out they have another issue with .cbr wrongly getting viewed as obfuscated rar (CBR/CBZ are, iirc, literally just rars and zips, they just have different extensions to indicate their contents). \n> \n> ```\n> 2025-07-16 17:05:50,911::DEBUG::[postproc:965] Detected volume-number 340 from RAR-header: /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr \n> 2025-07-16 17:05:50,915::DEBUG::[postproc:980] Deobfuscate: rarvolnr is: {340: {'/media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr': ['Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-000.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-...\n> Empire)/z.jpg']}}\n> ...\n> 2025-07-16 17:05:50,916::DEBUG::[postproc:995] Deobfuscate: Just one obfuscated rarset\n> 2025-07-16 17:05:50,916::DEBUG::[postproc:1000] Deobfuscate: Renaming /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr to /media/downloads/usenet/incomplete/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug/Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire) (cbr)-slug.r338\n> ```\n> \n> which is fallout of the .cbr being checked and viewed as a rar so when it does the rar header detection in rarvolinfo, it returning that its volume number is 340 (which then logic then goes oh it should be -2 so .r338) then that gets used to rename later on. \n> https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/blob/develop/sabnzbd/utils/rarvolinfo.py\n> \n> tried having them set cbr as ignore extension (config>special>ext_rename_ignore) but did not change the outcome as its not our actual deobfustication stuff but during the rar renamer \n> https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/blob/develop/sabnzbd/postproc.py#L963\n> \n> as .cbr are a little special we might want to guard against these from being checked in the rar_renamer to prevent this. which might end up resolving this other issue as well.. will piece this out to its own issue \n\n _Originally posted by @thezoggy in [#3113](https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/issues/3113#issuecomment-3079403472)_\n", "hints_text": "sab 4.5.2 - logs\n[sabnzbd-cbr.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21262614/sabnzbd-cbr.log)\ngrabbed example nzb from slug, and could replicate myself on windows box:\n```\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,005::INFO::[newsunpack:1041] Quick-check for Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr is OK, skipping repair\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,006::DEBUG::[filesystem:932] [sabnzbd.newsunpack.par2_repair] Deleting file \\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\incomplete\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr.par2\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,007::DEBUG::[filesystem:932] [sabnzbd.newsunpack.par2_repair] Deleting file \\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\incomplete\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr.vol0+1.par2\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,007::DEBUG::[filesystem:932] [sabnzbd.newsunpack.par2_repair] Deleting file \\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\incomplete\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr.vol1+2.par2\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,008::DEBUG::[filesystem:932] [sabnzbd.newsunpack.par2_repair] Deleting file \\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\incomplete\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr.vol3+3.par2\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,009::DEBUG::[filesystem:521] build_filelists(): joinables: []\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,009::DEBUG::[filesystem:522] build_filelists(): rars: []\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,009::DEBUG::[filesystem:523] build_filelists(): 7zips: []\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,010::DEBUG::[filesystem:524] build_filelists(): ts: []\n2025-07-16 12:12:40,011::DEBUG::[postproc:965] Detected volume-number 340 from RAR-header: \\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\incomplete\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr \n2025-07-16 12:12:40,013::DEBUG::[postproc:980] Deobfuscate: rarvolnr is: {340: {'\\\\\\\\?\\\\C:\\\\sab\\\\downloads\\\\incomplete\\\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr': ['Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-000.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-001.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-002.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire)/Howard The Duck (2015-) 003-003.jpg', 'Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackMan