r => \\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\complete\\test\\_UNPACK_Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr\n2025-07-16 12:24:05,964::DEBUG::[filesystem:896] Renaming \"\\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\incomplete\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr\" to \"\\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\complete\\test\\_UNPACK_Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\\Howard The Duck 003 (2015) (Digital) (BlackManta-Empire).cbr\"\n2025-07-16 12:24:05,966::DEBUG::[filesystem:896] Renaming \"\\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\complete\\test\\_UNPACK_Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\" to \"\\\\?\\C:\\sab\\downloads\\complete\\test\\Howard_The_Duck_003__2015___Digital___BlackManta-Empire___cbr\"\n```\nNice find.\n\n> CBR/CBZ are, iirc, literally just rars and zips\n\nYes!\n\nThat .cbr from OP's download:\n\n```\nsander@zwarte:~$ file something.cbr \nsomething.cbr: RAR archive data, v4, os: Win32\n\nsander@zwarte:~$ \nsander@zwarte:~$ hd something.cbr | hd | head\n00000000  30 30 30 30 30 30 30 30  20 20 35 32 20 36 31 20  |00000000  52 61 |\n00000010  37 32 20 32 31 20 31 61  20 30 37 20 30 30 20 63  |72 21 1a 07 00 c|\n00000020  66 20 20 39 30 20 37 33  20 30 30 20 30 30 20 30  |f  90 73 00 00 0|\n00000030  64 20 30 30 20 30 30 20  30 30 20 20 7c 52 61 72  |d 00 00 00  |Rar|\n00000040  21 2e 2e 2e 2e 2e 73 2e  2e 2e 2e 2e 2e 7c 0a 30  |!.....s......|.0|\n00000050  30 30 30 30 30 31 30 20  20 30 30 20 30 30 20 30  |0000010  00 00 0|\n00000060  30 20 30 30 20 61 39 20  38 30 20 37 34 20 63 30  |0 00 a9 80 74 c0|\n00000070  20 20 39 30 20 34 38 20  30 30 20 64 37 20 30 31  |  90 48 00 d7 01|\n00000080  20 31 66 20 30 30 20 36  31 20 20 7c 2e 2e 2e 2e  | 1f 00 61  |....|\n00000090  2e 2e 74 2e 2e 48 2e 2e  2e 2e 2e 61 7c 0a 30 30  |..t..H.....a|.00|\n```\n\nSee\"Rar\" in that output. That confuses `file` and SAB's rar finder. Even `unrar x something.cbr` does work and creates .jpg's. So a .cbr is a .rar file ... which we should indeed not handle as such. So: nice patch.\n\n`evince something.cbr` shows a comic book (with .CBR = comic book archive)\n\nFWIW: SABnzbd does not do funny things with .cbz\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/sabnzbd/sabnzbd/commit/70252ae167b1c0e3fd788bc2fd71a55912ba771f"], "created_at": "2025-07-16T17:28:17Z"}
